Amend SS/SCS/Senate Bill No. 1012 , Page 11 , Section 130.165 , Line 72 ,
2 by inserting after all of said line the following:
3 "324.049. 1. The board of registration for the
4 healing arts, the Missouri dental board, the board of
5 nursing, and the board of pharmacy shall not grant any
6 regulatory mitigation or waive or modify any rules related
7 to dispensing, prescribing, including prescription renewals,
8 administering, or otherwise distributing medications or
9 controlled substances to a person or business developing,
10 creating, or generating artificial intelligence for the use
11 of dispensing, prescribing, including prescription renewals,
12 administering, or otherwise distributing medications or
13 controlled substances.
14 2. As used in this section, the term "artificial
15 intelligence" means an artificial intelligence technology
16 system that:
17 (1) Is trained on data;
18 (2) Is designed to simulate human conversation with a
19 consumer through text, audio, or visual communication; and
20 (3) Generates nonscripted outputs similar to outputs
21 created by a human, with limited or no human oversight."; and
22 Further amend the title and enacting clause accordingly.
